Definition: a compound in which the hydrogen atoms of a hydrocarbon have been replaced by bromine and other halogen atoms
Example: very stable; used in fire extinguishers although it is thought to release bromine that depletes the ozone layer
Synonyms: organic_compound, pollutant, a, compound, in, which, the, hydrogen, atoms, of, hydrocarbon, have, been, replaced, by, bromine, and, other, halogen, very, stable, used, fire, extinguishers, although, it, is, thought, to, release, that, depletes, ozone, layer
Category: noun.substance
